E%D0%B2%D0%B8%D1%87.JPG\" width=\"177\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Старший преподователь</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ходжиев Рахим Муродович</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" height=\"248\" src=\"https://st.jtsu.uz/elfinder-files/test/%D0%90%D0%9D%D0%93%D0%9B%D0%98%D0%A1%D0%9A%D0%98%D0%99/%D0%A8%D0%B0%D1%80%D0%B8%D0%BF%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%B0%20%D0%A1%D0%B0%D1%80%D0%B2%D0%B8%D0%BD%D0%BE%D0%B7%20%D0%91%D1%83%D1%80%D1%85%D0%BE%D0%BD%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%BD%D0%B0.JPG\" width=\"177\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Старший преподователь</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Шарипова Сарвиноз Бурхоновна</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" height=\"248\" src=\"https://st.jtsu.uz/elfinder-files/test/%D0%90%D0%9D%D0%93%D0%9B%D0%98%D0%A1%D0%9A%D0%98%D0%99/%D0%AD%D0%B3%D0%B0%D0%BC%D0%BD%D0%B0%D0%B7%D0%B0%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%B0%20%D0%A4%D0%B5%D1%80%D1%83%D0%B7%D0%B0%20%D0%90%D1%85%D0%BC%D0%B5%D0%B4%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%BD%D0%B0.JPG\" width=\"177\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Учитель</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Эгамназарова Феруза Ахмедовна</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" height=\"244\" src=\"https://st.jtsu.uz/elfinder-files/test/%D0%90%D0%9D%D0%93%D0%9B%D0%98%D0%A1%D0%9A%D0%98%D0%99/photo_2021-06-23_09-27-27.jpg\" width=\"174\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Учитель</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ачилов Оятилло Кудратуллаевич</p>\r\n','<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>History of the Department of Foreign Languages</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The Department of Uzbek and Foreign Languages was founded in 1958. Initially, it was headed by Candidate of Philological Sciences, Associate Professor L. Kremsov, then M. Umarov and M. Finkelstein. Without exaggeration, we can say that the teachers E. Abdalina, L. Bikova, L. Lublinskaya, G. Fruminka laid the foundation of the department.During the period of work of the candidate of pedagogical Sciences, associate professor Radzhabov Bahodir Siddikovich, who headed the department from 1985 to 2006, the educational and regulatory documents were re-analyzed, the methodology of individual and general training with members of the national team was formed. . Guidelines and recommendations have been developed. Invaluable is the zeal and diligence of the teachers L. Livitskaya, L. Li, L. Krushinina, L. Novgorodova, D. Nugmonova, V. Ryabushkin, V. N. Kholkhodzhaeva, O. Shelyagina, R. Levina, E. Ivannikova, K. Lazarevskaya, Z. Annenkova, R. Vohidova, F. Khodzhaeva, V. Elizova, Z. Yuldasheva, B. Gainazarova, K. Korsunskaya, G. Kurbankulova and D. Yarasheva, who contributed a special contribution to teaching students Uzbek, Russian, English and German, developing their language skills, enriching their spiritual world through demonstrating the attractiveness of languages. In 1991, the department was named the Department of &quot;Uzbek and Foreign Languages&quot;. In 2006-2008, it was headed by Candidate of Philological Sciences, associate Professor Nodir Nasrievich Gafforov, in 2008-2014 - senior teachers Muborak Saidkarimovna Aikhodzhayeva, Yarasheva Dildora Nabievna. Since 2014, the department is headed by the candidate of Pedagogical Sciences, associate professor Feruza Rakhmatullayevna Norboeva. By the decision of the University Council of August 29, 2020, in September 2020, the department was reorganized under the name of the Department of &quot;Foreign Languages&quot;. Currently, the department has 33 professors-teachers, including 1 Candidate of Sciences, 9 senior teachers, 23 teachers and trainees. In the 2020-2021 academic year, the department conducts practical training in bachelor&#39;s programs in the areas of &quot;Russian Language&quot;, &quot;Foreign language&quot; and &quot;Applied English&quot;, in the master&#39;s program in the direction of &quot;Applied Foreign Language&quot;. At the initiative of the head of the Department, F. Norbaeva, students were taught German, French, Spanish and Korean. For this purpose, highly qualified specialists were involved S. Sobirov (German), M. Ashurova (French), T. Lee (Korean) and O.Achilov (Spanish), which aroused particular interest among students. It is thanks to the advice and direct assistance of the department staff that students have the opportunity to read and translate literature in their field, conduct research and actively participate in various conferences. As a talented young scientist, F. Norbaeva conducts significant work in the scientific and methodological, spiritual, educational and research areas of the department. Under her leadership, textbooks, monographs, more than a hundred scientific articles, theses and reports have been published. F. Norboeva regularly works on herself.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" height=\"506\" src=\"https://st.jtsu.uz/elfinder-files/test/%D0%90%D0%9D%D0%93%D0%9B%D0%98%D0%A1%D0%9A%D0%98%D0%99/JM_09734.JPG\" width=\"900\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">As a laureate of the grant of the Talent Fund for the training of promising young teachers and researchers of the President of the Republic of Uzbekistan, she completed a refresher course at the Shanghai University of China on the topic &quot;The use of information technologies in the educational process&quot;. According to the long-term plan of the department for the development of scientific potential for 2020-2023, according to the resolution No. 3 of the Scientific and Methodological Council of the Republican Center for Spirituality and Education of December 15, 2020, one of the young teachers of the department: - Sh.Sobirova, D. Rustamov and G. Botirbekova approved the topics of her dissertation works in the specialty 13.00.01. - &quot; Theory of pedagogy. History of pedagogical teachings &quot; for the degree of Doctor of Philosophy (PhD) in pedagogical sciences and was appointed scientific supervisor of the candidate of Pedagogical Sciences F. R.Norboeva.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p styl