 /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;Department of &quot;Sports Psychology and Pedagogy&quot; </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Department of Sports Psychology and Pedagogy of the Faculty of Adaptive Physical Education and Sport of the Uzbek State University of Physical Education and Sport was established in 1958 on the basis of the Department of Pedagogy and Psychology of the Uzbek State Institute of Physical Culture and Sports.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 2009, the department opened a bachelor&#39;s degree in psychology (sports) 5210202. Currently, 117 students are studying in this field. Since the establishment of the department, a teacher has successfully defended his PhD dissertation in pedagogical sciences. Currently, 3 teachers of the department are working on PhD dissertations, 2 - DSc dissertations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Department of &ldquo;Track and field athletics&rdquo;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Department of track and field athletics of the Uzbek State University of Physical Education and Sport was founded in 1955. Its first head of the department was Nikolai Nikolaevich Bykov (1955-1956, 1962-1966). L.A.Lebidiyanskaya (1956-1962), X.T.RAfiyev (1970-1974), G.G.Arzumanov (1975-1986), IA.Malikhina (1986-1987), K.T.Shakirjanova (1979-1995), E.R.Andres (1987-1999), Q.R.Qudratovich (1999-2001), T.R.Rasulova (2001-2004), L.V.Smuriygina (2004-2008), R.M.Matkarimov (2008-2010), N.T.Tukhtaboyev (2010-2013), M.S.Olimov (2013-2020) have been headed the department. From 2020 candidate of pedagogical sciences (PhD) I.R.Soliyev has being worked as the head of the department.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Today, some para athletics who have won a license for the Olympic Games in Tokyo such as Sukhrob Khodjayev - hurling, Mukhtasar Olimova - Shooting, Bobur Omonov, Izzat Turgunov, Bekjon Chevarov, Doniyor Ahmedov (master) are also studying at this department.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;Department of &ldquo;Sports Medicine and Biochemistry&rdquo; </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 1958, the Department of &quot;Sports Medicine and CPhE&quot; began its work at the Uzbek State Institute of Physical Culture and Sports, in 1961, the Department of &quot;Biochemistry and Hygiene&quot; was founded. The department of &quot;Sports Medicine and CPhE &quot; is headed by Candidate of Medical Sciences, docent A.H. Turakhodjayev, Candidate of Biological Sciences, Department of Biochemistry and Hygiene has been headed by docent L.V. Avanesova.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Department of &ldquo;Anatomy and Physiology&rdquo; </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 1955, the Department of Anatomy and Biomechanics was opened at the Uzbek State Institute of Physical Culture and Sport. The first head of the department was the founder of the School of Anatomy in Uzbekistan, a scientist in the field of anatomical sciences, a great pedagogue, Doctor of Medical Sciences, Prof. R.E. Khudoiberdiyev. Prof. R.E. Under Khudoyberdiyev&#39;s leadership, research was conducted in a number of important areas, and anatomy was created as a science in the Uzbek language.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Department of &quot;Adaptive Physical Education and Sports&quot; </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>On the basis of the Decree of the President of the Republic of Uzbekistan dated on December 1, 2017 No PF-5270 &quot;On measures to radically improve the system of state support of persons with disabilities&quot; from 2018, the department of Paralympic Sports was established at the State University of Physical Education and Sport. In 2019 the name of the department was changed to &quot;Adaptive Physical Education and Sport.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n',NULL,NULL,'photo_2021-06-19_15-10-21.jpg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'{\"meta_des_0\": \"\", \"meta_des_1\": \"\", \"meta_des_2\": \"\", \"meta_des_3\": null, \"meta_des_4\": null, \"meta_title_0\": null, \"meta_title_1\": null, \"meta_title_2\": null, \"meta_title_3\": null, \"meta_title_4\": null, \"meta_keyword_0\": \"\", \"meta_keyword_1\": \"\", \"meta_keyword_2\": \"\", \"meta_keyword_3\": null, \"meta_keyword_4\": null}',7,1624101856,1624682372,8,14,15,1,1,1),(38,2,'kurashfakulteti','Kurash fakulteti','Факультет борьбы','Faculty of wrestling',NULL,NULL,'<p style=\"margin-left:7.1pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:7.1pt; text-align:center\"><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;KURAS</strong><strong>H</strong> <strong>FAKULTETINING HAQIDA</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kurash fakultetining ochishdan asosiy maqsad 04.11.2020 yilda O&lsquo;zbekiston Respublikasi Prezidentining <strong>&ldquo;</strong><strong>Kurash milliy sport turini rivojlantirish va uning xalqaro nufuzini yanada oshirish chora-tadbirlari to&lsquo;g&lsquo;risida&rdquo;</strong>&nbsp; gi 4881- sonli qarori huquqiy asos bo&lsquo;lib xizmat qiladi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ushbu qarorda ko&lsquo;rsatilgan vazifalar <strong>Kurash fakultetining </strong>ham oldidagi asosiy ustuvor vazifa hisoblanadi. Bular:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Kurash bo&lsquo;yicha professional trenerlar, hakamlar tayyorlash, o&lsquo;quv-uslubiy qo&lsquo;llanmalar ishlab chiqish, kurashning ilmiy-metodologik bazasini kuchaytirish;</li>\r\n	<li>Aholining barcha qatlamlarini kurash bilan shug&lsquo;ullanishga keng jalb qilish hamda O&lsquo;zbekistonda kurashni umumxalq sport turiga aylantirish;</li>\r\n	<li>Yosh istiqbolli sportchilarni tanlab olish va tarbiyalash masalalari bo&lsquo;yicha bolalar-o&lsquo;smirlar sport maktablari, ixtisoslashtirilgan olimpiya zaxiralari maktab-internatlari bilan uzluksiz hamkorlikni amalga oshirish, ularga o&lsquo;quv-uslubiy va me&rsquo;yoriy-axborot yordam ko&lsquo;rsatishni ta&rsquo;minlash;</li>\r\n	<li>Kurashni aholi o&lsquo;rtasida, shu jumladan ommaviy axborot vositalari orqali keng targ&lsquo;ib qilish.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;Kurash fakulteti moddiy texnik bazasi;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:-7.1pt\">&nbsp; &nbsp;Kurash fakultetining moddiy texnik ba&rsquo;zasi yangi qurilgan k